Ever seen a coiled palm tree? 
Here’s a water study I did between gardening yesterday.

Though I painted her often, she never mentioned it, how she felt about me painting her. When she suspected I was excited by her posture or expression though, she would hold it perfectly while I fumbled for a camera in my bag. She was an artist herself and possibly knew that this was how she could support me in a very sneaky way, in silent agreement. And who knows! Maybe she actually hated that I painted her, but holding a pose is a very loving gesture.

Today is the last day to see 𝘛𝘩𝘦 𝘗𝘰𝘵𝘦𝘯𝘤𝘺 𝘰𝘧 𝘊𝘦𝘳𝘵𝘢𝘪𝘯 𝘎𝘦𝘴𝘵𝘶𝘳𝘦𝘴 at @sowandtailor. Hard to express what it meant to be included in this grand opening for my first lil solo show in Los Angeles. Thank you to everyone who has taken the time to see this work or has supported it from afar. I admit I am more sentimental about this body of work than usual, for reasons that are not mysterious to me at all. I have loved the experiences that led me to making this work, for how many failures it cost me. Thank you to @sowandtailor for including me in this  opening, a day I’ll never forget.

Saw someone on the water the other day and was sad I had no way to document him for later reference so I tried to take mental note of as many details as I could, and decided to draw today what I remembered about that moment. A mop of red hair against hazy purple cliffs, diffused blue sky, skin so light pink it was almost blue, his slouched posture and shivering back, a hint of dark defeat in his eyes as he impatiently awaited the next set.
